Actually, after your clarification, I think the previous dashboard-oriented design is not the right primary screen.

Your product sounds more like a Data Gap Resolution Workbench than an ESG dashboard.

The user journey should be:

Select Dataset/Table
        ↓
Find Missing Fields
        ↓
Choose Company/Records
        ↓
Generate Proxy Recommendations
        ↓
Compare Alternatives
        ↓
Approve Proxy
        ↓
Write Back to Temporary Table
        ↓
Track Until Vendor Data Arrives

This workflow should be the center of the UI.


